<title>UK: Lynx bid talks with Kalamazoo at early stage.</title>
<headline>Lynx bid talks with Kalamazoo at early stage.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-06-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Lynx Holdings, the UK provider of communications and computer systems and services, said on Wednesday that it was in initial bid talks with Kalamazoo Computer Group Plc.</p>
<p>&quot;The board confirms that whilst talks with the Kalamazoo board have taken place, discussions are at a very early stage and may or may not lead to an offer being made for Kalamazoo,&quot; the company stated in response to recent newspaper speculation</p>
<p>It promised to keep shareholders informed of relevant developments.</p>
<p>-- London Newsroom +44 171 542 7987</p>
